Definition.WordDefinition: Transporter \Trans*port"er\, n. One who transports. [1913 Webster]

transporter n 1: a long truck for carrying motor vehicles [syn: {car transporter}] 2: a crane for moving material with dispatch as in loading and unloading ships 3: a moving belt that transports objects (as in a factory) [syn: {conveyer belt}, {conveyor belt}, {conveyer}, {conveyor}]
